          "schema": {
            "type": "string",
            "contentMediaType": "application/octet-stream",
            "title": "Horizon Profile",
            "description": "Upload a horizon profile file in `JSON` or `CSV` format. The file is automatically parsed and validated. Returns processed horizon profile data for the specified geographic location.\n\n\n- `JSON` format: requires `horizon_height` array (0-90° or 0-π/2 radians), optionaly a `units` field (`degrees` or `radians`, defaults to `degrees`)\n    - Optionally provide also `azimuth` array (0-360° or 0-2π radians, must match `horizon_height` length). In other case the azimuth will be inferred from the `horizon_height` array starting from North (0°) and going clockwise.\n    - Minimum 4 values required.\n\n- `CSV` format: comma-separated horizon height values.\n    - Similar to `JSON` format.\n    - Minimum 4 values required.\n\nExamples:\n\n- JSON in degrees: [horizon_profile.json](../assets/horizon_profile.json)\n- JSON in radians: [horizon_profile_radians.json](../assets/horizon_profile_radians.json)\n- CSV in degrees: [horizon_profile.csv](../assets/horizon_profile.csv)"
          }
