    "summary": "Calculate the heating and cooling degree days",
    "description": "Compute heating and/or cooling degree days for a given location and period.\n\n## Spatial Coverage\n\nView the coverage map using the [🗺️ Interactive Coverage Viewer](./coverage/map)\n\n## Features\n\n- Heating and/or cooling degree days in a **single call** by selecting the `mode`\n  parameter (`heating`, `cooling`, or `all`).\n- Flexible temporal aggregation via the `period` parameter:\n  daily, weekly (ISO week), monthly, or yearly degree days.\n- Arbitrary time series supported by\n  [Pandas' `DatetimeIndex`](https://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/reference/api/pandas.DatetimeIndex.html)\n  through the `timestamps` dependency.\n- Configurable base temperature (`heating_threshold`, `cooling_threshold`) and\n  cut-off (`heating_cutoff`, `cooling_cutoff`) in °C.\n- Output units selectable via `temperature_output_units` (`C`, `F`, or `K`).\n- Results available as **JSON** (default) or as an in-memory **CSV** attachment\n  (`csv` query parameter).\n- Optional **fingerprint** of the results for reprod…",
